 ;; DECIDED (@019f221f-8f10): free dotted names ARE rejected on the nix target.
 ;; A dotted name `root.a.b` descends into an attrset, so its ROOT must be a
 ;; binding in scope (nix/module formal, let, param, nix/with-cfg alias, or the
 ;; nix global `builtins`); a root bound nowhere emitted `${root...}`, which
 ;; nix-instantiate --parse rejects as an undefined variable — a silent
 ;; miscompile. The checker now rejects it at check time (E021 free-dotted-name,
 ;; check.rkt `check-nix-free-dotted!`), mirroring nix's own --parse scope check
 ;; and exempting `nix/with` dynamic scope. The old nix-interp-ms entry is gone:
 ;; that fixture's `vendor.id` is now let-bound (a valid ambient descent), and a
 ;; dedicated reject row (nix-free-dotted) pins the E021 rejection. Zero nix
 ;; divergences remain.
 []}
